<body>
<p><u>Will I always get great pictures of my baby?</u> Unfortunately, we will not know until the time of the ultrasound. Babies all have different personalities and sleep at different times. It’s best to come in during your baby’s active time, follow the appointment tips and come in during the recommended timeframe. The key to success seems to be the necessary water intake, we recommend drinking 2 liters of water daily for 5 days before your ultrasound. It’s always a good idea to purchase a package that includes a free redo if needed.</p>

<p><u>When is the best time to see your baby?</u> Please view our Ultrasound Calendar for standard recommended timeframes, please read the below exceptions.</p>

<p><strong>If you have an anterior placenta (placenta in front of baby’s face) it is best to schedule your appointment for earlier in your pregnancy, between 24-27 weeks</strong>. The best viewing time for twins is 24 to 26 weeks. Click your due date on the calendar, then refer to the shaded date ranges and the detailed descriptions below. If you are over 200 pounds we recommend waiting until you are at least 30 weeks gestation and drink 2 liters of water daily for at least 7 days prior to your appointment.</p>

